{"id":14881404,"mediaExerciseId":"4c95f9d5-a579-4285-9d1a-1da46ca05c8e","exerciseName":"5","chapterName":"13","chapterTitle":"Return, Risk, and The Security Market Line","groupId":612376,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":452,"solutions":[{"id":5994833,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we are asked to determine the expected return. \n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/ea94df9a8637bccc7ada47dd8f8bcee6/3ed5c721beaecff505394f762a23b735/lateximg_large.png","width":842},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/ea94df9a8637bccc7ada47dd8f8bcee6/3ed5c721beaecff505394f762a23b735/lateximg.png","width":420}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The **expected return** is the net income or loss that an investor predicts on investments given known interest rates.\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/ea94df9a8637bccc7ada47dd8f8bcee6/962cf3a797bb149b1039171b78f8fc47/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/ea94df9a8637bccc7ada47dd8f8bcee6/962cf3a797bb149b1039171b78f8fc47/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's first identify the given amounts in the problem: \n\n\n| | Amount$\\hspace{5pt}$| \n|:--|--:| \n|Recession: ||\n|Probability return | 20% | \n|Portfolio return |-8.00%|\n|Boom: ||\n|Probability return | 80%| \n|Portfolio return|15%|\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":136,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/ea94df9a8637bccc7ada47dd8f8bcee6/76d5eb84aa58943827fe72819ab4cf37/lateximg_large.png","width":1049},"regular":{"height":70,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/ea94df9a8637bccc7ada47dd8f8bcee6/76d5eb84aa58943827fe72819ab4cf37/lateximg.png","width":525}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"The **expected return** is computed as follows: \n\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Expected return}&=\\sum_{\\text{}}{\\text{}_{R}} {\\text{PR $\\times$ R}}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nWhere: \n\nPR = Probability return \\\nR = Return","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":220,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/ea94df9a8637bccc7ada47dd8f8bcee6/86429d77d7ff76ec828470b06506b586/lateximg_large.png","width":702},"regular":{"height":110,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/ea94df9a8637bccc7ada47dd8f8bcee6/86429d77d7ff76ec828470b06506b586/lateximg.png","width":351}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"First, let us insert the provided data to the formula from step 4. As an illustration, here's what it looks like: \n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Expected return}&= {\\text{[20\\% $\\times$ (-8.00\\%)] + (80\\% $\\times$ 15\\%)}}\\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":144,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/ea94df9a8637bccc7ada47dd8f8bcee6/7499708eb4521b51696de3b8bd851119/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":73,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/ea94df9a8637bccc7ada47dd8f8bcee6/7499708eb4521b51696de3b8bd851119/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"Now, let us compute the portfolios's expected return. This is computed as follows: \n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Expected return}&= {\\text{[20\\% $\\times$ (-8.00\\%)] + (80\\% $\\times$ 15\\%)}}\\\\\n&={\\text{(-1.60\\%) + 12\\% }}\\\\\n&={\\textbf{10.40\\%}}\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":221,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/ea94df9a8637bccc7ada47dd8f8bcee6/93005d16b71d24b7464843215de47ee1/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":112,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/ea94df9a8637bccc7ada47dd8f8bcee6/93005d16b71d24b7464843215de47ee1/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"**To conclude, the expected return is 10.40%.**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":7}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"7ac0aefc-36c1-4c61-9196-ad74e3c4068f","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":7}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881405,"exerciseName":"6","page":452,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"0990c097-26db-438e-a88e-c7ffbc6332cb","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-13-questions-and-problems-6-0990c097-26db-438e-a88e-c7ffbc6332cb"},{"id":14881406,"exerciseName":"7","page":452,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"d555d692-bacf-450d-9c6f-940cf499f031","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/tex